						<summary>

						<p>On a slab lying near the ruined Mātangēśvara temple in the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1172, Sādhāraṇa, Pushya, ba. 15, Sunday, Ardhōdaya, corresponding to 1251 A.D., January 23.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of a perpetual lamp to the temple of Mātaṅgēśvara by a certain Tailapa-Nāgana for the merit of his parents, on the occasion of Ardhōdaya.</p>						

						</summary>
